 Early Beginnings  The crew - hard at work - while we wait for the planter to prepare our rows for us.    Joe delegates the setting out of our row markers. Howard&rsquo;s mind is blown.    Really a beutiful day to be outside!    Row 202 - the extra special, very picturesque row.   Timelapse of the planting of a row:
Set out 17 foot guideline &#10004;
Plant seeds along 8 inch marks &#10004;
Gently cover seed with soil &#10004;
Repeat 330 times&hellip; &#10004;
 Timelapse of the planting of an entire range. (An hour compressed into 22 seconds of frantic hand planting!)  Credit: Range timelapse by Joseph Woomer.
